I'm the boss of Mondays around here, ya see.

It's a really warm spring day here in the burgh.  I decided that I wanted a more business look, so suit it was.

The thing that I like about suits in the spring/summer is that there's little to choose.  You pick the suit, shirt, tie and shoes.  My accessory choices aren't abundant (not a huge accessory guy). You put it all on and go. It's like a uniform really.  A little creative interpretation, but not enough to overwhelm me.  My casual kits actually take way more work.

It feels like life is starting to go back to being busier.  The kids have more practices/events, weather is warming up, projects are increasing, and work has been really busy the past couple of months.

I liked the slow pace of quarantine life. Did I miss people? Absolutely.  Do I want to go back to the non-stop hustle? Absolutely not.

Remaining hopeful that I'll be able to strike a nice balance of active, but still have a slower frequency.  How are y'all feeling about the creep of the return of life?

Have a kick-ass day guys!  Hope that your weekend were all wonderful! #dapperpgh
